int32 CFS_ComputeCRCFromFile ( uint32  FileHandle,
uint32 *  CrcPtr,
uint32  TypeCRC 
)

Compute CRC from a file.

Description
This function will compute the cyclic redundancy check (CRC) value of data in a file
Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
The computation starts from the current location of the file pointer to the end of file
Parameters:
[in] FileHandle The open file handle of the file to scan
[in] CrcPtr Where to store the computed CRC.
[in] TypeCRC One of the enumerated CRC types supported by the CFE_ES_CalculateCRC function
[out] *CrcPtr The computed CRC. Only updated if the return value is OS_SUCCESS
Returns:
Returns OS_SUCCESS if no error
The return code from OS_read if an error occured
See also:
CFE_ES_CalculateCRC, OS_read

boolean CFS_IsPacketFiltered ( CFE_SB_MsgPtr_t  MessagePtr,
uint16  FilterType,
uint16  Algorithm_N,
uint16  Algorithm_X,
uint16  Algorithm_O 
)

Determine whether Software Bus message packet is filtered.

Description
This routine will apply the CFS filter algorithm to the packet to determine whether the packet should be filtered. This same algorithm may be used by multiple applications (DS, TO, etc.)
Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
None
Parameters:
[in] MessagePtr Pointer to a Software Bus message packet
[in] FilterType Packet sequence count (1) or timestamp (2)
[in] Algorithm_N Algorithm parameter N "pass this many"
[in] Algorithm_X Algorithm parameter X "out of this many"
[in] Algorithm_O Algorithm parameter O "at this offset"
Returns:
Returns TRUE if the packet should be filtered (not used)
Returns FALSE if the packet should not be filtered (used)
See also:
CFS_IsPacketFiltered

boolean CFS_ResolveSymAddr ( CFS_SymAddr_t *  SymAddr,
uint32 *  ResolvedAddr 
)

Resolve symbolic address.

Description
This routine will resolve a symbol name and optional address offset to an absolute address
Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
If the symbol name is a NUL (empty) string, then the offset becomes the absolute address
Parameters:
[in] SymAddr A CFS_SymAddr_t pointer that holds the symbol name and optional offset
[in] ResolvedAddr A pointer to the location to store the resolved address in
[out] *ResolvedAddr The fully resolved address. Only valid if the return value is TRUE
Returns:
Returns TRUE if the resolution was successful
Returns FALSE if the resolution was not successful
See also:
OS_SymbolLookup

uint32  Size 
)

Verify 16 bit alignment.

Description
This routine will check an address and data size argument pair for correct 16 bit alignment
Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
None
Parameters:
[in] Address The address to check for proper alignment
[in] Size The size in bytes to check for proper alignment
Returns:
Returns TRUE if both Address and Size are 16 bit aligned
Returns FALSE if either Address or Size is not 16 bit aligned
See also:
CFS_Verify32Aligned
